<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[264,1323,398,745]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,439,518,544]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The new species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="(Song, 1991)" authorityName="Zhang &amp; Zhu &amp; Song" authorityYear="2005" baseAuthorityName="Song" baseAuthorityYear="1991" box="[772,1174,519,545]" class="Arachnida" family="Oxyopidae" genus="Hamataliwa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="labialis">
<emphasis box="[772,1013,519,544]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Hamataliwa labialis</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Song, D. X." box="[1029,1165,519,545]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" pagination="169 - 181" refId="ref6780" refString="Song, D. X. (1991) On lynx spiders of the genus Oxyopes (Araneae: Oxyopidae) from China. Sinozoologia, 8, 169 - 181." type="journal article" year="1991">Song, 1991</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
in the heartlike depression of female epigynum, but can be easily distinguished from the latter in copulatory ducts of female epigynum short, spermathecae oval (
<figureCitation box="[968,1039,599,625]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[265,1323,794,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-176@6.[253,1335,784,1737]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hamataliwa cordata sp. nov., 6–8, female holotype. 6, body, dorsal view; 7, epigyne, ventral view; 8, vulva, dorsal view; 9–10, male paratype. 9, male left palp, ventral view; 10, male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 6, 1.0mm; 7–10, 0.2mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Fig. 8</figureCitation>
); tip of median apophysis of male palpal organ round, conductor complex, with four distal processes, ventral tibial apophysis large and hammer­like, retrolateral tibial apophysis almost rectangular with a small process (
<figureCitation box="[519,646,719,745]" captionStart="FIGURES 6–10" captionStartId="6.[264,382,1763,1787]" captionTargetBox="[265,1323,794,1725]" captionTargetId="figure-176@6.[253,1335,784,1737]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 6–10. Hamataliwa cordata sp. nov., 6–8, female holotype. 6, body, dorsal view; 7, epigyne, ventral view; 8, vulva, dorsal view; 9–10, male paratype. 9, male left palp, ventral view; 10, male left palp, retrolateral view. Scale bars: 6, 1.0mm; 7–10, 0.2mm." pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Figs. 9–10</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
